1. Executive Summary
A black-box penetration test was conducted against the CorpNet Network Operations Centre (NOC) web portal hosted at 10.xxx.xxx.xxx. The assessment identified a chain of critical vulnerabilities that, when combined, allowed unauthenticated access to the server followed by full root-level compromise.
The attack path required no special tooling beyond standard HTTP requests, an SSH client, and a common password wordlist. An attacker with basic web exploitation skills could reproduce these results in under 30 minutes.
Root cause: The application was built without parameterised queries, relied on a bypassable blocklist for input sanitisation, stored credentials in plaintext configuration files, and protected a sensitive credential vault with a dictionary-guessable master password.
