4.4 Credential Discovery and Initial SSH Access
Two sets of credentials were recovered using the command injection primitive:
From `/opt/netops/secret.config` (readable by `www-data`):
```ini
[backup_agent]
run_as   = sysadmin
password = XXXXXXXX
```
From `/opt/netops/app.py` (source code, readable by `www-data`):
```python
pw = hashlib.md5(b"XXXXXX").hexdigest()
```
This revealed the plaintext password `XXXXXXX` for the `netops` application account.
The backup agent password was tested against the `sysadmin` OS account over SSH:
```bash
ssh sysadmin@10.XXX.XXX.XXX
Password: XXXXXXX
```
Result: Successful authentication as `sysadmin` (UID 1001).
User flag retrieved from `/home/sysadmin/user.txt`:
```
THM{}
```
